inn1.comm: very full and outside off, angling away further. Warner simply lets it pass. Watling nearly gloves it in front of first slip. Off-side wide
full on middle and leg, hangs back and works it through square leg. Munro moves to his left, swoops down on the ball, but can't flick the stumps down. Finch responded well
pitched up and right in the channel outside off, Southee finds some outswing, Finch covers his off stump and shoulders arms
leg-side wide now, against the right-hander. Full and angled down leg
similar length, slipping down leg, brushes the pad and rolls behind to the keeper
another full one on the leg stump, flicked uppishly to the right of the square-leg umpire
full and holds its line on middle, Warner presses forward and pushes to mid-off with a dead-straight bat
back of a length on middle, Warner is back and across as he turns it to midwicket
full and pushed across the right-hander, who lets it pass to Watling

full and straightens, but not enough. Boult searches for some inswing, Finch plays around his front pad, and falls over the flick. This was clearly heading past the leg stump. Finch weathers the lbw shout
back of a length on off, chopped out to the covers
short on off, not any room to free his arms. Chopped to point now

Another failure for Finch, he picks out Nicholls to perfection at shortish square leg. Good length and Boult finds inswing again. Finch looks to thump it down the ground from outside off with no feet, he can only drag an inside edge, which carries to Nicholls. That looked ungainly from Finch
good length and slanted across Smith, left alone in the channel
excellent ball. Pitches on middle and skirts away past the outside edge. Wobbles through to the keeper. Southee attempted a cross-seamer. It hit the deck and curved away past the groping bat
chopped down to the covers
good length and holds its line outside off, Warner chases an expansive drive and does not make contact. Nothing on snicko. No bat involved
back of a length and slanted across off, Warner has a wild slash at it and misses
pitched up and outside off, gets forward and push-drives straight to mid-off
Warner has timed the pants off this. Full and outside off, not a half-volley, he eases forward and drives it through the covers, placed to the left of Santner
dug in shorter and outside off, glided to point
fullish on off or just a shade outside off, patted into the covers
short and angling across off, dabbed with soft hands to backward point
very full and fired across off, 137ks, too wide. Smith reaches out, but can't touch it
pitched up and outside off, driven on the front foot straight to extra cover
back of a length and outside off, Smith punches firmly on the back foot, Guptill dives to his left and stops it

Boult strikes again. After bowling six deliveries on off or outside off, Boult brings this one back into the hips with the angle from around the stumps. Teases Smith to flick, despite the presence of two catching midwickets and a shortish square leg. The Australia captain shuffles across off, but can't keep it down. He holes out to Nicholls too at shortish square leg, falling into the leg-side trap. He goes for a seven-ball duck
dug short on middle, short-arm pulled away to backward square leg
short and wide outside off, slapped away with disdain, Santner dives full-length to his right and intercepts the ball
back of a length and outside off, pushed into the covers
118ks slower short ball outside off, Warner plays a checked-push to the covers
dug short and outside off, Warner controls a pull to deep square leg
very full on middle and leg, flicked away in the gap between midwicket and square leg
shortish and angled into the hips, deflected to square leg
back of a length and angling away outside off, Bailey leaves it be
back of a length and outside off, punched to extra cover
short and outside off, holds his elbow up, and punches crisply to extra cover
dug in short on off, Bailey hops, gets into an awkward position from that side-on position, half-fended, half-swatted to square leg
short and wide outside off, Bailey has width to free his arms. Square-cut away
full and hung up wide outside off, Bailey shoulders arms
full, angled in, and swerves away. Bailey is squared up as he wafts loosely and is beaten
full on off, Bailey is on the move as he taps the ball down to mid-on
full and angled in on the stumps, prodded to mid-on
short and wide outside off, throws his hands at a cut and skews the ball to extra cover
full on the stumps, pushed down to mid-on
full on off, defended
similar ball on off, Warner is right forward to push it to extra cover
Warner shimmies out, meets a full ball, and whips it through square leg
full and angled across off, left alone
bumper on the leg stump. Bailey rocks his head out of the way. Flies over to the keeper. Too high. Wide
back of a length on off, Bailey hangs back and punchily blocks it back to Boult
banged short on middle, hops up and pushes down the ground, straight of mid-on
full on off, 141.1ks, starts with a front-foot no-ball. Tapped square towards point. Big no-ball
122.1ks slower short ball on middle, Bailey backs away outside leg, slogs early. Skews it off the inside half to midwicket
148ks, full-toss outside off, driven down to mid-off
short and angled in, 145.6ks, pulled away to square leg
146.8ks, full, pushed back down the pitch
146.6ks, short and outside off, Bailey with his front leg pointing to extra cover, eventually leaps off his feet as he meets the pitch and jabs to extra cover
swish and a miss outside off, Bailey is beaten for pace
A short extra cover, a wide slip, point, and mid-off in place. Length ball on off, Warner goes over the top. Slapped over extra cover
similar ball on off, pushed with a straight bat to extra cover
short and angled on off, swatted away to midwicket
full and angling away outside off, push-driven to mid-off
short on off stump, hip-high ball, pulled away to the right of square leg
back of a length on off, played back to the bowler. Quiet Powerplay for Australia, just three boundaries in it
short on off, 150.2ks, pace like fire. Warner is late on it, the ball comes down at an angle. Nearly chopped on, like he did in Sydney
150.9ks, length ball on off, drives to mid-off, and takes Williamson on
148.8ks, short and outside off, hops and punches to extra cover
pace like fire, again. 152.1ks, back of a length and zings away outside off, Warner is late on it again
bouncer, angling away, 143.6ks, Warner lets it pass over him. Too high, wide
very full on off, 150.2ks, pushed to mid-on
slower ball, 127.4ks, overpitched and outside off, flat-batted forcefully straight down the ground
pushed outside leg, goes down on one knee and sweeps it to short fine leg
tosses it up on off, pushed down the ground to mid-off
down the track and whipped straight to midwicket
dangled on middle stump, Warner steps away outside leg and plays a late-cut to short third man
glanced off the pads through the square-leg region
looped up on off, Bailey gets into a more side-on position as he meets the ball. Driven down to long-off
back of a length on off, 148.8ks, punched to extra cover
overpitched and outside off, 151.1ks, sliced away behind point
short on off, 149.3ks, swat-pulled to long leg
very full on middle, 146.2ks, not a yorker, jabbed out to the covers

Nicholls hurtles in from deep midwicket, gets into a side-on position, then dives, but can't latch onto the chance, or the half-chance. The ball goes through the hands. Banged in short and angling away outside off, Warner does not hold back. He pulls but miscues it, and gets away
looped up and outside off, Warner goes over the top. Hits through the line over mid-off for a six, the first of the game
pushed to the off side
nudged to the leg side
worked to square leg
down the track and whipped through midwicket
looped up on a fourth-stump line, defended
short and angling away outside off, 147.3ks, steered to third man
short and angled in at the body, hops and fends the ball to midwicket
full, angled in, then snakes away past the outside edge. Bailey doesn't have enough time to move his feet
short and outside off, 150ks, hops and punches to cover
back of a length and outside off, 146.3ks, sliced off an outside edge, does not carry to backward point
146ks bouncer on the middle stump, Bailey ducks under it. Adjudged to be too high by umpire Llong. Wide
length and outside off, 147.4ks, squeezed down to third man
flatter and drifts into Bailey, who has a back-foot force at it, nearly spoons a return catch
leg-stump full-toss, paddled to long leg
slides in on middle, quicker, clips the inside edge and rolls back down the pitch
Bailey uses his feet, but is he beaten in flight. Inside-edged to short fine leg
looped up, push-driven back, Santner dives to his left and stops the ball
quicker through the air, Bailey leaves the crease, gets close to the pitch, but plays across the line, and squirts an inside edge onto the pad
length and outside off, sliced through point
full and outside off, pushed on the front foot through the covers
just short of a good length on off, Bailey stands up tall and punches back to De Grandhomme
leg-side wide, past the attempted glance of Bailey
back of a length and angled in on off, Bailey closes the bat-face and hits the ball to long-on
veering into the hips, flicked in the air to the left of midwicket
hip-high short ball on off, swatted away to  short fine leg, and that's drinks
flat and Santner runs this across Warner, who jumps back and lashes a cut behind point
length ball, angled in on middle, played back to Santner with a straight bat
Santner held this back in the air, dips late in its flight, check-driven down to long-off
worked from a middle-and-leg line to square leg with a closed bat-face
slower through the air on the leg stump, glanced finer of square leg for one now
pushed outside off, Bailey brings out the reverse-sweep, finds short third man
back of a length and angled into the hips, picked off to long leg, excellent diving save from Henry to his left in the deep. Keeps it to two
sliding into the pads again, glanced behind square

soft ball, soft dismissal. Spooned to midwicket. Early Christmas present for Santner and de Grandhomme. Good length holds its line on off, the batsman perhaps plays a bit early and lobs a simple catch. Santner did not even have to budge
back of a length and just outside off, tapped to point

De Grandhomme strikes twice in three balls. Marsh could consider himself unlucky. Just short of a good length and on off stump. Marsh is cramped for room as he aims to punch through the covers. But he is stapled to the crease He manages a thick inside-edge, which hits the front leg and then ricochets onto the top of the stumps
back of a length and outside off, nicely punched on the back foot to extra cover
slides on with the arm, backs away, chops from the stumps towards point
tossed full on off, driven smoothly to long-off on the front foot
flighted and outside off, stabbed through the covers
flatter on middle and leg, punched past Williamson's right
flatter and fired across off, Head forces on the back foot, chops and finds point
much slower through the air, pushed to extra cover on the front foot
full and on the pads, clipped away to short fine leg. Head calls for the run from the non-striker's end and manages to bat the throw at the wicketkeeper's end very narrowly
fuller ball, dabbed into the leg side
wider fuller ball outside off, Head slashes and short cover runs in to cut it off
length ball outside off, no pace, just 114kph, defended off the backfoot to the right of the bowler
similar length ball but a lot straighter and around off this time, blocked off the backfoot back to the bowler
fuller ball on the fifth-stump channel, Warner presses forward and gently caresses it wide of mid-off for a quick single
width on offer outside off and Head shapes up for a cut shot. But the ball is a bit too full and does not bounce enough for Head who gets beaten
this time he nails the cut shot as it's wide and gets up to his liking as well but can't pierce the packed off-side field as cover-point dives across to cut it off
full and straight on the stumps, clipped off the pads to midwicket
good length ball outside off, Head slaps hard and the ball goes to cover-point
full and outside off, it's a tempter and Head blindly goes after it trying to pull off a slog from nowhere. No feet from the batsman and he gets beaten
swing and a miss again. Sees the width and tries to slap it. But he is a long way away and can't put bat to ball
defended back to the bowler
length ball on the stumps, defended to the leg side
sprays it down the leg side and the wicketkeeper who is standing up to the stumps, does well to get down to his right and cut it off
good length, angling in on middle and leg, tucked off the pads through midwicket
width on offer, Head opens up his arms and finds point on the cut
good length outside off, Head rides the bounce before opening the face of his bat to run it down to third man
shorter ball at 110.9kph, Warner comfortably turns it away to midwicket off the backfoot
short ball, Warner rolls his wrists over the pull shot to keep it along the ground, midwicket intercepts it
short of a length and angled across at a slower pace outside off, Warner steers it to third man with an open bat face
Head struggling here. It's a wide ball and Head has another swing and misses outside off
that's better. Does not go at it with hard hands. Just waits for this ball outside off and opens his bat face late to run it down towards third man
short ball, Warner fetches the pull from outside off and rolls his wrists over the shot to control it as the ball goes to deep midwicket
good length just outside off, Warner taps it to backward point. No run there
short of a length outside off, slightly quicker this time at 123.1kph, Head opens the bat face and steers it to third man
angled in on a length, Warner pushes it off the front foot into the off side
fuller and on the stumps,worked away off the pads to long-on
fuller ball, drilled down just wide of mid-off for a quick single

short ball outside off, Warner fetches the pull from outside off and swats it wide of long-on who runs across but the ball beats him comfortably. That's the fifty for Warner and also the first boundary since the 14th over
tucked to square leg off the pads
steered to square third man
short ball, Head leans back and ramps it well wide of the wicketkeeper before the ball is cut off at the third man bounary
full and outside off, Warner cracks a drive through covers. Does not get across which gives him enough width to free his arms and the ball shoots through the extra cover region
short of a length, tucked off the pads through square leg
short ball, Head tries to lean back and play the upper cut but the bounce is too steep and he is beaten
moves across to cover his stumps a tad too early. That perhaps cramped him slightly for room as he picks out point on the cut shot to this short of a length ball that is angled across outside off
short of a length ball, angled in from around the stumps, worked to point
back of a length outside off, punched off the backfoot just wide of point who dives to his left to cut it off but they get enough time to complete the single
this time, Guptill at point nflings himself to his right to cut off this slap from Head to a short and wide ball
short and wide ball, Head slaps it away uppishly to sweeper cover

Warner comes on to the front foot to this short of a length ball and tries to punch it. Does so uppishly inciting cries of "catch it." But the ball lobs just over the leaping cover fielder and goes away to sweeper cover
bouncer from Ferguson, too high and called a wide
short ball, Head lays into a pull shot and the ball races away between long-on and deep midwicket
moves across early to cover his stumps. It's pre-meditated. The ball was wide and outside off. It's slower also and takes forever to get to Head who gets beaten as he attempts an awkward slap
goes too hard at it and knocks this length ball outside off to mid-off

short ball juust around off, pulled away to cow corner. Two fielders - deep midwicket and long-on - give it a chase and converge on the ball. The former puts in the dive to just about pull it back before the ropes. They go upstairs to check and he seems to have done fine there
short and wide, slapped hard to point
moves across his stumps early before trying to tuck this back of a length ball off the hips to the leg side. Calls for a run but is denied by Warner
shorter ball, punched off the backfoot to sweeper cover
fuller ball, Head goes with hard hands at the drive and ends up closing the face of the bat, skews the ball to the leg side
presses forward and pushes this fuller ball to mid-off before calling for a quick single. Direct hit would have had him there
eased down to long-on
opens the face of his bat to tap to backward point
short and wide ball, steered away to square third man
short of a length ball, punched off the backfoot to sweeper cover
slightly shorter in length and Head brings out the pull but the ball does not bounce as much and he cannot make contact
good length outside off, Head swats it with a flat-bat to point
uncomfortably pulls after partially ducking to this short ball that is angled down leg, the ball goes behind square
waits for it before steering this ball between point and backward point
fuller ball around the fifth-stump channel, punched off the front foot to short cover
short of a length outside off, Warner cuts and gets it off the bottom part of the bat to extra cover
defended back to the bowler
fuller ball, angled in on the pads, pushed down to long-on
poor delivery. Shorter on length and down the leg side, Warner turns around and trickles it past short fine leg
fuller ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot
full and on the off-stump channel, Warner drops it in front of cover for a quick single

lucky boundary, that. It wa sshort and wide outside off. Cross-seam delivery does not bounce as much as he would have liked and Warner gets a bottom edge that beats the diving wicketkeeper and races way to the fine leg boundary
gets an inside edge again and skews it to square leg this time

what a shot! Absolutely bludgeoned. You offer width at the pace outside off, it's going to go to the boundary nine out of 10 times. Head was struglging with his timing and wasn't able to find the middle of the bat. But that muct have felt good. Lays into the cut shot and the ball goes away to the square third man boundary
angling in from over the wicket, Head gets an inside edge on to his pads and the ball rolls away to the leg side
tucked to the leg side
short ball outside off, Warner responds with a pull but does not make contact
tucked to midwicket
short ball outside off, Head can't find the middle of the bat on the cut and the ball goes to cover
full ball, eased straight down the ground past the bowler who slides and sticks his hand out but can't stop it

close run out chance at the striker's end. It was a short ball and Warner pulls it just wide of short fine leg. Trent boult does not send the best of throws at the striker's end or Travis Head could have been in trouble. It was Head's call and he makes it in the end
fuller on middle and leg, flicked away to midwicket
steered down to third man
shuffles across and cuts this short and wide ball. But there is a point and a backward point. Too packed there and he can't pick the gap
very full and outside off, knocked powerfully down the ground to long-off
short ball, Warner swivels around with the pull to deep midwicket. Momentarily thinks of a second run but it went straight to the fielder there so they decide against it

great running. It was full and outside off. Head drilled it hard to mid-off but did not time it precisely. Williamson fires a throw at the non-striker's end as they scamper across for a quick sinlgle. Does not hit the stumps and there is no back-up as they take a quick second run and Head has to put in the dive to get back in the crease
short of a length ball, Head inside-edges the pull to the pad and Ferguson darts forward on the follow-through to ensure there is no run
length ball, angled in on the stumps, tries to push it to the off side off the front foot and ends up inside-edging it
tucked to midwikcet
short of a length outside off, punched off the backfoot to short cover
fuller outside off, driven to sweeper cover

oh, what a shot. That was unorthodox but so effective. It was a length ball outside off and Warner flat-bats it off the backfoot straight down the ground. Nigel Llon ghas to jump out of the way as the ball shoots past him and past the straight boundary
short ball, pulled to deep square leg
pushed across on a length outside off, Warner makes room for himself before punching it through covers, picks the gap perfectly
slightly shorter ball and some width on offer, cut square of the wicket
stays back to this length ball and eases it off the backfoot to long-on
fuller ball, drifting across from around the wicket, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot
tucked off the backfoot to square leg
fuller outside off, driven firmly but straight to cover
fuller ball on the fourth-stump channel, driven wide of mid-off for a quick single
fuller ball a set of stumps outside off, Head shuffles across and squeezes out a drive to cover
goes for a wild slog across the line to this fuller ball and gets comfortably beaten. It was a cross-seam delivery and he was probably done in by the lack of pace on that delivery

fuller ball, driven firmly and rather uppishly towards mid-off. Head sets off for a quick single and the ball lands just in front of Williamson who fires in a throw at the non-striker's end. He misses but a direct hit would have seen the back of him
fuller ball outside off, driven to cover
short ball, Warner swivels around and pulls it past the diving fielder at backward square leg
makes room to get close to the line of the ball before tucking it to deep square leg

oh, lovely shot. Gets it very fine and the ball goes away to the fine leg boundary. That's Warner's seventh ODI century. Only Tendulkar (nine in 1998) has more in a calendar year. Coming to the delivery, it was a length ball that didn't spin much. Warner tucks it off the pads and it seems like the ball would go to the short fine leg fielder. But he places it superbly and gets it very fine as the ball beats the short fine leg fielder who tries to chase it down
tucked to the leg side
fuller ball, driven to long-on and that is the 100 of the partnership
nudged to the leg side for a single
stays back to this length ball and knocks it to the left of the bowler who gathers it on the follow-through
short of a length ball, punched off the backfoot but mistimes it to mid-off. Takes off for a quick single and completes it
short ball, angles across. Head moves across towards the off-stump in a pre-meditated move before ducking to get under the ball
moves across again to meet this fuller ball that's fired wide outside off, crunches a square drive but the ball is fielded at point where the fielder makes a diving save
still can't beat point. Short of a length and Head slaps it but Latham this time dives to his left to cut it off
short ball, pulled away to deep square leg. There is a man at deep backward square leg stationed, and he moves across to gather it before the boundary
moves across to protect off-stump before steering it to third man

pre-meditated. Good delivery from Santner. Head moves across perhaps looking for an expansive shot through the off side. But Santner gets it to drift away from around the stumps and Head is far away from the line of the ball as a result. It does not turn much either, so he can't get anywhere close to it and the ball crashes into the stumps
floated and pushed across on a length outside off, blocked
good length ball on middle stump, Wade tucks it to the leg side

ooh, that was a loopy delivery drifting down leg. Not too far away from the leg stump and Wade cannot make contact as he tries to get it behind square. The wicketkeeper takes the bails off after collecting it but his foot was inside the crease. Called a wide
fuller outside off, squeezed out to mid-off
tucked behind square
gets down to sweep early and just guides it towards backward square leg on one knee as Santner bowls a full toss
full on middle and leg, whipped into the vacant spaces at midwicket
back of a length and outside off, punched to cover-point
full on off, worked with the wrists to midwicket
whipped away to the left of midwicket
full on the stumps, stabbed down the ground as Warner is cramped for room
length and outside off, clipped through midwicket
nurdled off the pads to midwicket
breaking into the pads, fuller length, worked wide of midwicket
Warner brings out the reverse-sweep. Tossed up on middle, Boult pre-meditates moves to his left at backward point, but this is placed fine of the fielder
quick fizzer on middle, forced to mid-off
clipped off the hips to the left of midwicket. They hare back for the second
straight ball on middle, patted straight to Williamson at extra cover
too full and straight, 112.3ks, whipped through midwicket

Warner clears long-on.  Just short of a good length on middle, Warner unleashes a front-foot pull, nay a golf-swing over long-on. Boult flies to his right from long-on, but the ball sails over him. Boult flies over and lands beyond the ad boards

shortish and outside off, Warner unleashes a rasping pull. Puts Munro over the boundary again, clears a leaping deep midwicket now. #MCG not big enough for Warner. Is Williamson regretting the Munro experiment?
Warner drills this flat and straight, does not carry to long-on
back of a length and outside off, chopped to the covers
full on middle and leg, whipped away through midwicket
Wade shimmies down the track, the bowler adjusts his length. Short, picked off through the midwicket region
full on the stumps, Warner backs away outside leg, and bashes the ball through the covers
pitched up and outside off, driven firmly to Williamson at extra cover
pretty full on off, whipped past midwicket's left

the bails simply refuse to budge. Back of a length, cramps Wade for room. He gets an inside edge, which drops near his feet, and rolls back onto the stumps. Wade tries to stop it with his bat, the ball hits the stumps, but the bails stay put. "No, no" says Watling, and smiles wryly
short and outside off, flat-batted over Boult
full-toss outside off, over the waist, Wade leaps and flat-bats it over cover-point
Warner dispatches the free-hit. Poor length ball outside off, slower too, Warner clears his front leg, and launches it over long-on for a massive six. Smoked
short and outside off, short armed away wide of midwicket
slower short ball on middle, swatted away to long leg
banged in on leg stump, pulled to long leg
leg-stump yorker, nearly 146ks, squeezed out past midwicket
Warner backs away outside leg, this is speared outside off. Warner knows he has no chance of reaching it. Left alone
lobbed up on middle, goes low and paddles the ball to short fine leg
Wade pre-meditates a slog-sweep. Santner is smart with his variations in pace. He held this back, 78ks. Wade gets it high on the bat and holes out to deep midwicket
whipped from off stump past Santner's left
tossed up on off, worked through vacant mid-on. Warner hares across for the second
much slower on off, dabbed to cover with an open face
speared outside off, 93ks, jabbed to the same fielder
full and wide outside off, reaches out and carves it over point
slower ball on leg stump, 103.8ks, tickled to short fine leg
sprayed wide outside off, Warner reaches out, but can't make contact
slower short ball outside off, flat-batted in front of long-on. Warner turns quickly, and hurtles back for the second
Southee cuts his fingers across this slower delivery as well. Warner fetches it from outside off and blasts it in the air to the left of mid-off, who is up
115ks, cutter outside off, short, swatted away over square leg
114ks, banged into the middle of the deck, sails through to the keeper. Warner pulls hard and swings himself off his feet. He is surprised that isn't called a wide
yorker on middle, dug back to the bowler
full and just outside off, slapped away to extra cover
back of a length and outside off, just 116ks, chopped away to extra cover
110.ks slower short ball outside off, Warner, having shuffled away outside leg, waits for the ball to arrive, leaps, adjusts and then carves it over backward point.  Reaches 150
Warner backs away outside leg, Boult swings a yorker into the left-hander. Beaten
very full and slanting outside leg, Warner misses the glance, brushes the pad and sneaks away fine past a diving Watling
cutter on off, 103.9ks, stabbed to extra cover
slower lifter on middle, top-edged pull, does not carry to long leg
another cutter on middle stump, Faulkner picks it up and pulls to deep midwicket
pretty full and outside off, jabbed down to mid-off
down the track, gets a short slower ball, pulled over midwicket
Warner moves away outside leg, this is pushed wide outside off. Reaches out and slices it over the covers. Warner  scampers back for the second. Top class running

Warner hares on for the second, the throw is to the striker's end. Faulkner is in. Low full-toss on middle, hit down to wide long-on. Watling collects the ball in front of the stumps and swipes the bails off, but Faulkner is home
full and outside off, Faulkner sizes it up and smites it down the ground with a flat-bat, straight of long-on
full and just outside off, Faulkner plonks his front leg forward and swings early, slower delivery from Boult.  The batsman skies a catch to long-on
yorker on leg or just outside, backs away and carves the ball square through the off side
Warner flits outside leg again, this is forced back to the left of the bowler. Boult stretches his left hand out, spins around for a throw at the stumps, but slips over

Boult splatters the stumps at the non-striker's end and catches Warner short from the last delivery of the innings. Pinpoint yorker just outside leg, Warner, having backed away outside leg, jams it towards short extra cover. Boult runs in, then to his right, and throws the stumps down. Excellent work

inn2.comm: length and angling away outside off, cracked straight to backward point
140.2ks inswinging yorker, jammed back to the bowler
back of a length and thuds into the thigh as Guptill hops and does not make contact with a flick
good length and swings into the leg stump, 142.9ks, Guptill squirts an inside edge onto the pad as the ball sneaks away square on the leg side
pitched up on off and middle, Latham leans forward and flicks in the gap at midwicket for three runs
full and angling away outside off, driven on the front foot to mid-off. Mis-hit
nice and full, hint of inswing, nibbles back in, tight leave. Narrowly shaved the off stump
full and angled across the left-hander, sneaks past the outside edge. Shooter. Rolls through outside off. Wade drops down on one knee to collect the ball
full and swings in inside-edged onto the pad
full and angling away outside off, left alone
full and angling away outside off, presses forward and drives the ball to extra cover
back of a length and slanting away outside off, guided past slips to third man
leg-side wide, swinging down leg
full and holds its line outside off, skids on, Latham covers his off stump and ignores it. Wade gloves the ball in front of his boot
full and swerving down the leg side, Latham shuffles across and misses the flick. The noise came from the bat hitting front pad
full and outside off, 145.6ks, Latham leans into the drive and sends the ball racing away through the covers
left alone outside off
short on off, worked to midwicket
full on off, swings away a touch, pushed to cover on the front foot
lifting ball on middle, 141.7ks, hops and glides it to point
good length and angling away outside off, blocked to midwicket on the front foot
Latham leaves the crease, takes a half-volley and belts a drive straight of mid-off. Shot
full and swings in a touch, he plays around his front pad, flicking wide of midwicket
back of a length on the stumps, played back to the bowler
length and angled across off, left alone
slanted down leg, another wide. Wade dives full-length to his right to glove the ball
left alone outside off
fuller ball just outside off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, angled across off, Guptill stands tall and punches elegantly off the backfoot through covers. The ball is pulled back before the ropes and they have enough time to complete three
fuller ball on the fourth stump channel, Latham presses forward and blocks to covers
fuller ball, angling down leg, Latham picks it up off the pads and heaves it through midwicket. The ball is fielded in the deep

fuller ball on the fifth-stump channel and that's a beautiful stroke from Latham. Presses forward and gets right to the pitch of the ball before gently caressing it through extra cover. Just timed it and used the pace on the delivery
steered to third man with an open bat face
good length ball on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
length ball, angled across on the fourth-stump line, blocked from the crease
width on offer, Latham tries to steer it away but goes at it with hard hands and ends up doing so uppishly before the ball is fielded at third man
fuller ball on leg and middle, clipped off the pads to midwicket
fuller on the fourth-stump channel, Guptill presses forward and quietly defends towards cover

short of a length ball, Guptill pulls it off the hips and gets his front leg up and across as he rides the bounce, the ball is cut off before the backward square leg boundary by the fielder in the deep
short of a length ball on leg and midde, Latha closes the face of his bat early as he looks to nudge it to the leg side and the ball skews off the leading edge towards point on the bounce
back of a length on the leg stump channel, tucked comfortably off the pads to deep fine leg
short of good length outside off, Guptill blocks from the crease and the ball goes off the inside part of the bat to the right of the bowler
back of a length outside off, Guptill gets on top of that and punches elegantly off the backfoot but straight to cover
length ball, angling in on the pads, tucked to midwicket
fuller ball, pushed to mid-on for a sharp single

Guptill uses the angle on that delivery well. It was short of good length and angling in from just outside off. Guptill shifts back slightly to get on top of the bounce before flat-batting it wide of the diving mid-on fielder
good length, outside off blocked
waits for this length ball outside off before deftly opening his wrists late although he can't beat backward point
slightly shorter in length outside off. Latham skips down a step and as a result is late on the pull shot and chops it on to the turf as the ball goes back to the bowler.
back of a length, tucked off the pads behind square on the leg side
good length on off, defended to covers from the crease
short of a length and angled across, Latham's eyes light up on seeing the width on that delivery as he slaps but the ball goes to point
fuller ball outside off, Latham pushes it off the front foot and drops it in front of mid-off who is slightly deep
back of a length outside off, Guptill punches off the backfoot just to the right of cover who dives to stop the ball
fuller ball outside off, driven along the carpet to mid-off
well-directed short ball that forces Latham to lean back and drop his wrists as the ball is left alone in the channel just outside off

oh, dear! Picks out square leg on the flick. It was a good length ball and Latham used the angle well to flick it. Timed it to perfection but could not place it as he would have liked. The ball goes straight to Faulkner at square leg. Simple catch and Latham's promising innings comes to an end
fuller ball, angled in to the right-hander from around the wicket, Guptill closes the face of his bat and gets a leading edge as the ball goes to the off side
full and outside off, driven firmly but straight to extra cover
good length ball, attacking the stumps, knocked back to the bowler
short of a length and angled in, Guptill gets an inside-edge to the pad on the attemped flick
length ball that is angled in on the pads, Guptill glances it to the fine leg boundary
good length outside off, blocked into the off side
short ball, Williamson ducks and it's too high, so called a wide
short of a length outside off, Williamson punches it square of the wicket off the front foot and what a save at backward point. George bailey flings himself to his left with both hands outstretched
beautiful placement. It was full and on the pads. There is enough pace on that delivery and all Williamson has to do is find the gap which he does as he nudges the ball wide of mid-on

good length on the fourth stump channel, Williamson defends it very late off the front foot, so late that the ball lands  right on the crease and goes behind the stumps, to the right of the wicketkeeper
fuller outside off, driven to cover
good length outside off, steered to third man
jumps back to ride the bounce before trickling it away towards the third man region
fuller ball outside off, angled in on off, defended back to the bowler
fuller and on the pads, tucked away to square leg
good length and angling in, turned away with the angle behind square
fuller ball on the fourth or fifth-stump channel, pushed off the front foot past the diving extra cover fielder to long-off
very full ball outside off, Williamson has to reach out for it but does well to drive it square of the wicket, picks the gap between cover-point and backward point

fuller ball, again defends it very late and drops it at the crease as the ball goes behind the stumps. The wicketkeeper has to move across slightly, towards gully, to collect it and that gives them enough time to take a quick single
width on offer outside off, Williamson waits for it and opens the face of his bat to guide it to third man
short ball, well-deceived slower ball. Guptill is through with the pull shot much earlier than earlier and the ball goes to the wicketkeeper
short of a length and angling in, Guptill tucks off the hips to deep fine leg
good length on off, Guptill comes on to the front foot and defends late and the ball goes to gully
back of  length outside off, steered to third man with an open face. Guptill calls for the quick second and scampers back to beat the throw which is slightly wayward
short of a length, angling in on the hips, tucked to the leg side
fuller ball on the stumps, pushed carefully back to the bowler
short of a length outside off, punched off the backfoot to long-off
full and angling in from outside off, defended with the angle towards mid-on
back of a length, tucked with the angle to deep square leg
back of a length ball outside off, punched easily from the crease to sweeper cover

and the on-field decision stays. It was a short of good length ball that was angling. Williamson moved across to get outside the line of the ball and flick it away to the leg side. But he perhaps moved away too much and ended up playing around the pad and the ball hits the front pad. Nigel Llong raised his finger but Williamson reviews it. Only way this can get overturned is if the angle takes it down leg. It is quite sharp but it seems as though it will be umpire's call. In fact, it's hitting the inside of the leg stump

Smith tries to pull off a repeat of the blinder he snaffled in the previous match but this time does not manage to do it. It was a short ball and Guptill flays it hard past Smith who is diving to his right but can't get his hands to it
length ball outside off,  Guptill knocks it to mid-on
nudged through square leg
good length ball, shaping away, left alone in the channel outside off
fuller and outside off, defended
shifts across to protect his off-stump before blocking this length ball off the backfoot into the off side

oh, what a catch! It's Bailey this time. Didn't fling himself full length like Smith in the previous match, but it was a remarkable catch nonetheless and very tough. It was fuller outside and Guptill could not keep his drive along the ground. The ball lobs over the head of Bailey at short cover and he leaps up to snaffle it. Timed his jump to perfection and his back formed an almost uncomfortable arch as he took it. Guptill is livid. New Zealand now need to be careful
punched off the backfoot straight back to the bowler
good length ball, Munro allows himself some room before slapping it away to sweeper cover
short and wide outside off, slapped away wide of sweeper cover who puts in the dive to cut it off
drops it in front of the gap between cover and point and scampers across for a single
fuller ball, the ball goes towards mid-off after an inside-edge to the pads
pushes Munro back with a short of a length delivery which the batsman knocks back to the bowler
fuller and outside off, driven to covers
very full ball outside off, Nicholls jams his bat down and drills it hard into the turf before the ball goes to the bowler
short of a length outside off, steered to backward point
good length ball outside off, defended

oh, gone. That's the perfect yorker. There aren't too many bowlers in world cricket today who bowl that delivery better than Starc. It was an attacking line and on the stumps. Nicholls was looking to bring his bat down to squeeze it out but the ball swings in late to beat the bat and rattle leg stump
darted in, chopped from the stumps to backward point
tossed on middle, paddled away behind square
full on middle, pushed back to the bowler
shorter and outside off, cut through the covers
short and hurled on off, played back to Head
looped up on middle and leg, shuffles across and clips to square leg
length and outside off, 142.5ks, Munro is beaten for pace
back of a length on off, glides it off the face to backward point
back of a length and cuts away outside off, slower one. Munro jabs at it and manages an inside edge onto the pad
half-volley outside off, leans forward and drills it away. It seemed destined to race to the boundary... until Head dived full-length to his right to stop the ball at extra cover
low full-toss, tails in, jammed out to midwicket
slower bouncer, tennis-ball bounce, Munro hunkers down and lets it sail over him
flighted outside off, goes low and sweeps it to long leg
straight ball on the leg stump, driven to long-on on the front foot
tossed-up offbreak, turns in, dabbed with the spin behind square
follows it with a slider heading for middle stump, chopped on the back foot through the cover-point region
turning offbreak, tucked away to deep backward square leg
flatter and fired on middle, drills a drive to long-off
back of a length on middle, late-cut to short third man
rapid yorker, swings in late, Munro is beaten for pace and is smacked on the pads outside leg
full and angled in on off, Watling opens the face and dabs the ball to backward point
very full and holds its line outside off, Watling slices it to the left of backward point
half-volley outside off, flat-bats a drive to extra cover. Can't get past Bailey
140.8ks full missile outside off, Munro swishes and misses. Think the batsman was late onto it
fired across off, back-foot punch back to Head
short on leg stump, pulled straight to short fine leg
looped up on middle, Watling plays early, nearly chipped a catch to midwicket
this is pushed outside the leg stump, swept fine of short fine leg for four

an appeal for lbw, not given. Did it straighten enough? It may have pitched outside leg. Smith and Head converge and challenge the on-field call. RTS does not detect an inside edge. It pitched in line, hitting off stump. Three reds flash on the big screen. Umpire Llong's on-field call is reversed. Watling attempted to sweep again, but made no contact this time
down the track and whipped fine of long leg
short and outside off, slapped through cover
nip-backer, back of a length, de Grandhomme is pinned on the thigh. This was bouncing over the stumps
back of a length on off, pushed to cover
back of a length and outside off, glided to backward point
full on middle, patted to the right of extra cover
short on middle, Munro hops and rides a single to third man
short on middle, hangs back and whips to midwicket
driven down to long-off from outside off
full and Head runs this one across the right-hander, hit firmly to long-off running in
short and wide outside off, hammered away to deep cover
De Grandhomme races down the track, meets the pitch, and lofts it straight down the ground. Dumps Head over the sightscreen
speared on middle, "oh my goodness" screams Wade behind the stumps, as the inside-edge wanders away to long leg
short on off, quelled to point
back of a length on off, back-foot punch to extra cover
full and angled in on off, front-foot drive back to the bowler

Head probably was late to pick up the ball. He runs in from deep square leg, dives forward, and pouches it. It jams the fingers under the ball; Head clings onto it nevertheless. Clean catch. NZ six down and sinking. Dug in short and outside off, De Grandhomme swivels on the back foot. Pulls and miscues it to the fielder
good length and Hazlewood runs this one past the outside edge
full and angling away outside off, left alone. Rounds out a wicket-maiden
slides in quick and takes the pad
short on middle, flat-batted to long-on
tossed on middle, dabbed to extra cover on the front foot
opens the face and punches from outside off to Warner at backward point
short and outside off, punched between backward point and cover
chopped from off stump to Smith at extra cover
short on off, hangs back and fends it to cover
full and angling away outside off, driven to mid-off
back of a length and outside off, punched to backward point
short on middle, cramps him for room. Stabs an inside edge to square leg
full on off, pushed down the ground
speared on middle, punched to extra cover
Munro sees flight, he likes it, takes it from middle stump and smears it over the bowler's head
shorter and outside forced on the back foot to sweeper cover
chopped from outside off through the cover-point region
speared on leg, punched on the back foot through the covers
very full, slants in on leg, flicked away through midwicket

rip-roaring reverse-swinging yorker. Late inward shape for the fast bowler. Clatters into the leg stump. Every time Smith wants to break the stand, he turns to Starc, and his bowler delivers.  Munro attempts a whip or a drive, and is beaten for pace. The ball shot through even before the left-hander could bring his bat down
edged, but does not carry to Wade. Full, angled in, swings away, opens Southee up. He wafts and nicks it. Wade dives to his right, but the ball drops in front of him
very full and angled in on middle, Southee, having cut down his backlift, keeps it out
low full-toss, angled in, and curves away. Pushed to cover
back of a length and outside off, guided to backward point
swish and a miss outside off
good length on off, played back to the bowler
dabbed to backward point
glanced off the pads, deflected fine on the leg side four four
length and outside off, pushed to cover
full awayswinger outside off, poked down to third man off an outside edge
middle-stump yorker, 145ks, reverses in, kept out
Santner backs away outside leg, Starc shortens his length and goes outside off. Santner swings hard and does not connect
very full on the pads, Starc overshoots it, chipped in the air over square leg
Santner moves away outside leg, Starc follows him, the batsman pushes and outside-edges it through the vacant cordon
not quite a yorker, very full and reverses in, Santner plays down the wrong line, and is beaten for pace too. Trapped in front of middle
good length, angling in from outside off, Southee skips down a step and knocks it back to the bowler
fuller ball outside off, driven into the covers region
comes down the track early and the bowler adjusts by shortening his length. Southee is forced to steer it to point
comes down the track again and goes for a wild slog but it's a length ball and the back-of-the-hand slower one which Southee does not pick and he gets beaten
short of a length, defended into the leg side
comes down the track early again and the ball follows him which aids Southee as he lofts it over the on side with the angle. Does not get enough on it though and the ball is fielded at deep midwicket
fuller ball, angling in on the stumps from outside off, defended

Smith claims a catch at slips and it's not given. It certainly carried to Smith at second slip who dives forward and takes it. It was a short ball and Southee was trying to drop his wrists and back away. But the ball goes off the back glove, on to the forearm and lobs towards Smith. Australia review it and replays show that the back hand had come off at the point of contact, so the on-field decision stays
full and wide, Ferguson backed away and took himself well outside the line of the ball. Can't make any contact
low full toss just inches outside off. Ferguson uncomfortably shifts back in his crease and the ball shoots past the outside edge
fullish ball outside off. Ferguson awkwardly shuffles across and keeps it out off the backfoot
fuller ball outside off, swing and a miss from the batsman
comes down the track and looks to slog but the bowler follows him by firing it on leg stump channel and Southee ends up getting cramped for room as he makes no contact
fetches it awkwardly from outside off and swats it to long-on
short of a length ball, back-of-the-hand slower variation. Ferguson dabs it uppishly into the vacant region around forward short leg

Southee's chancy stay comes to and end with a miscue to extra cover. It was the slower ball and Southee was forward looking for a big hit over long-off. The lack of pace means he does not get the timing right and he skews it off the high end of the bat to Warner who settles under it at extra cover
runs it down to third man with an open face
very full ball outside off, squeezed out to cover
fuller ball, chips the drive to cover-point where Cummins dives forward and takes it on the bounce
fuller ball, angled in on middle from around the wicket, pushed to mid-on
sprayed down leg, clipped away to fine leg
fuller ball outside off, sticks his bat out without feet and knocks it to the off side
yorker on the stumps, Boult jams his bat down and squeezes it out. The bat face opens as it makes contact with the ball and it goes to the off side
fuller ball, Boult awkwardly keeps it out to covers. Again, no feet
back-of-the-hand slower ball that's angled across on a length outside off, Ferguson tries to cut and misses
similar delivery and this time Ferguson skips down the track and tries to cut, again misses
fuller ball, driven uppishly to covers and it drops short of the fielder there
short of a length, tucked with the inward angle to fine leg
good length outside off, comes forward and defends it to point
full and on the pads, Boult backs away and whips it to midwicket

oh, what a way to finish! It's Smith again. Took a stunner in the previous game. This one's as good if not better than the one in the previous ODI. He dived to his left on that occasion; this time, flings himself full-length to his right to snaffle a blinder at second slip. It was a slower back of a length ball from Cummins and Boult backs away and looks to open the face of his bat to steer it. Gets himself into an awkward position and skews it off a healthy outside edge
